            <title>[KAFKA-2852] Kafka Authroizer CLI should use consistent way to specify multiple values for all config options.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2852</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, AclCommand uses inconsistent conventions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For principals, we take &lt;br/&gt;
--allow-principal User:Bob --allow-principal User:Alice&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For other options like hosts, we take&lt;br/&gt;
--allow-hosts Host1,Host2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should have a consistent way to specify this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
